name: CreateBlogTagsBatch
description:
Create multiple blog tags in a single request.

This tool is used to create multiple blog tag objects as specified in the request body. Call this tool when you need to add several blog tags at once to a HubSpot CMS blog.

parameters.name: blog_tags_json
parameters.description: A JSON array detailing new Blog Tags to create, with fields like name, language, and ID.

deletedAt.description: The timestamp (ISO8601 format) when this Blog Tag was deleted.

language.description: The explicitly defined ISO 639 language code of the tag.

id.description: The unique ID of the Blog Tag.

translatedFromId.description: ID of the primary tag this object was translated from.

value_schema.description: The JSON array of new Blog Tags to create.

metadata.description: Tools that enable LLMs to interact directly with the hubspot_cms API.

value_schema.description: The JSON array of new Blog Tags to create.

secrets.description: The OAuth token to use for authentication.
